description: From Latin superincumbentem, present participle of superincumbere.

adjectives.description: superincumbent (comparative more superincumbent, superlative most superincumbent)

entries.meaning: (chiefly sciences) Lying or resting on something else; overlying.
examples: As the vapour cooled the water would be precipitated, and an ocean would surround the spherical nucleus with a superincumbent atmosphere.
